race.comment: Good race with a host of win chances. Sticking with the progressive SMOTHER (4) who has had only ten starts but now out in journey is really putting it together. Last start just missed on the main track and looks hard to beat this longer trip. DOLCEMENTE (9) was safely held last time but worth another chance. Went back from a wide gate and never came on but drawn far better here. Best figures stack up and gets chance to atone. COORONG TYCOON (2) is another worth another try. Was going well leading into the Strathalbyn Cup and was safely held in that. This is much easier and can improve sharply. CLASSY CLARET (5) is in form winning an easier contest at the provincials last time. Progressing well so don't underestimate.
